[1] Saudi Arabia, 6 new cases - MOH 2-17 Apr 2018
Date: Tue 17 Apr 2018
Source: Saudi MOH 2-17 Apr 2018 [edited]
https://www.moh.gov.sa/en/ccc/pressreleases/pages/default.aspx


According to the spreadsheet data I have been keeping, the most recent information available is current as of 17 Apr 2018:

There have been a total of:
1827 newly confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infection, including
738 reported fatalities [reported case fatality rate of 40.4 per cent]
1076 recoveries, and
13 currently active cases [those who have not been reflected in reports of fatalities or recoveries]

Since the last update (through 1 Apr 2018) there have been:
6 newly confirmed cases
3 newly reported fatalities
9 newly reported recoveries

[Note that during the period 9-16 Apr 2018 there were no reports on the Saudi MERS website, but information was added retroactively on 17 Apr 2018. Also, note that exposure histories refer to the 14 days preceding onset of illness. - Mod.MPP]

Information on newly confirmed cases (6 cases):
- None of the cases were healthcare workers.

1- Reported as 15 Apr 2018: A 93-year-old Saudi male from Alqunfodha (Al Qunfudhah) [Makkah region] noted to be in stable condition. Classified as a primary case with high risk exposure history still under investigation.
https://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/statistics-2018-04-15-001.aspx

2- Reported as 12 Apr 2018: A 69-year-old Saudi female from Hufoof [Ash Sharq朝yah - Eastern region] noted to be in stable condition. Classified as a primary case with high risk exposure history still under investigation.
https://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/statistics-2018-04-12-001.aspx

3- Reported as 12 Apr 2018: A 43-year-old expat male from Najran [Najran region] noted to be in critical condition. Classified as a primary case with a history of direct contact with camels.
https://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/statistics-2018-04-12-001.aspx

4- Reported as 8 Apr 2018: An 85-year-old Saudi male from Haweiyah [Makkah region] noted to be in stable condition. Classified as a primary case with a history of direct contact with camels.
https://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/statistics-2018-04-08-001.aspx

5- Reported as 4 Apr 2018: A 57-year-old expat female from Riyadh [Riyadh region] noted to be in stable condition. Classified as a secondary case in a household contact.
https://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/statistics-2018-04-04-001.aspx

6- Reported on 2 Apr 2018: A 58-year-old Saudi male from Najran [Najran region] noted to be in stable condition. Classified as a primary case with high risk exposure history still under investigation. Reported as a recovery on 7 Apr 2018 [see recovery no. 5 below].
https://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/statistics-2018-04-02-001.aspx

Information on newly reported fatalities (3 fatalities):
- None of the cases were healthcare workers.

1- Reported as 17 Apr 2018: A 43-year-old expat male from Najran [Najran region] with history of pre-existing co-morbidities [reported as a newly confirmed case on 12 Apr 2018 at which time he was noted to be in critical condition. Classified as a primary case with a history of direct contact with camels. - Mod.MPP]
https://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/statistics-2018-04-17-001.aspx

2- Reported as 14 Apr 2018: A 44-year-old expat male from Hufoof [Ash Sharq朝yah - Eastern region] with no history of co-morbidities [reported as a newly confirmed case on 24 Mar 2018 at which time he was noted to be in critical condition. Classified as a primary case with history of direct contact with camels. - Mod.MPP]
https://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/statistics-2018-04-14-001.aspx

3- Reported as 10 Apr 2018: A 64-year-old expat male from Riyadh [Riyadh region] with a history of pre-existing co-morbidities [reported as a newly confirmed case on 23 Mar 2018 at which time he was noted to be in critical condition. Classified as a primary case with high risk exposure history still under investigation. - Mod.MPP]
https://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/statistics-2018-04-10-001.aspx

Information on newly reported recoveries (9 recoveries) [information not available on 2 of the recoveries - Mod.MPP]
- Only 1 of the reported recoveries is a healthcare worker

1- Registered on 11 Apr 2018: no information available on the Saudi MOH website

2- Reported as 10 Apr 2018: A 41-year-old Saudi female from Jeddah [Makkah region] with a history of pre-existing co-morbidities [reported as a newly confirmed case on 24 Mar 2018 at which time she was noted to be in stable condition. Classified as a secondary case in a household contact. - Mod.MPP]
https://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/statistics-2018-04-10-001.aspx

